{"type":"message","id":"9826e65e","parentId":"558fa149","timestamp":"2026-03-18T10:39:03.536Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking what problems would occur if both Feishu accounts are bound to main.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. Two Feishu accounts (coder account and main account) are configured\n2. Both are routed to main agent\n3. This means whichever message comes in, it goes to main\n4. The coder agent doesn't actually get used\n\nProblems:\n1. Wasted resources - coder agent exists but isn't used\n2. Can't distinguish between different Feishu accounts\n3. Can't route different users to different agents based on account\n\nBut wait - the user said they want each agent to have its own Feishu. Let me think about what the actual routing issue might be.\n\nLooking at the binding config:\n- coder <- feishu accountId=coder\n- main <- feishu accountId=main\n\nThis should route based on accountId. But maybe there's a conflict because both are using the same \"feishu\" channel?\n\nActually, looking at the logs earlier, it seems like feishu[default] is being used. The accountId routing might not be working properly because the channel might not be specifying which account to use.\n\nLet me explain the potential issues to the user.","thinkingSignature":"609a54e8f196d4da4f2d11741552aab738f580cee91b7275f76c117d9f513c39"},{"type":"text","text":"两个飞书账号都绑定到 main 的问题：\n\n| 问题 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| **1. coder 浪费** | coder Agent 创建了但没用，一直空闲 |\n| **2. 无法区分用途** | 不同的飞书账号没有对应不同的 Agent |\n| **3. 路由冲突** | 两个绑定都是 feishuchannel，可能互相覆盖 |\n\n**理想情况：**\n- main 账号 → main Agent（通用对话）\n- coder 账号 → coder Agent（编程任务）\n\n**当前情况：**\n- 两条消息都进了 main Agent\n\n需要我重新调整绑定，让 coder 专门处理编程问题吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":72,"output":385,"cacheRead":40121,"cacheWrite":82080,"totalTokens":122658,"cost":{"input":0.0000216,"output":0.00046199999999999995,"cacheRead":0.0012036299999999998,"cacheWri