                |\\n|           |                                     | you need to post tweets, reply, quote,        |                    |\\n|           |                                     | search, read posts, manage followers, send    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | DMs, upload media, or interact with any X     |                    |\\n|           |                                     | API v2 endpoint.                              |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? browser                          | Automate web browser interactions using       | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | natural language via CLI commands. Use when   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | the user asks to browse websites, navigate    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | web pages, extract data from websites, take   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | screenshots, fill forms, click buttons, or    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | interact with web applications.               |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? cron-mastery                     | Master OpenClaw's timing systems. Use for     | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | scheduling reliable reminders, setting up     |                    |\\n|           |                                     | periodic maintenance (janitor jobs), and      |                    |\\n|           |                                     | understanding when to use Cron vs Heartbeat   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | for time-sensitive tasks.                     |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? desktop-control                  | Control desktop applications on Windows ??    | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | launch, close, focus, resize, move windows,   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | simulate keyboard/mouse input, manage         |                    |\\n|           |                                     | processes, control VSCode, read clipboard,    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | and capture screen info. Use when the user    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | wants to interact with any running program,   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | switch windows, type text, press shortcuts,   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | open files in VSCode, manage running          |                    |\\n|           |                                     | processes, or get system display information. |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? memory-setup                     | Enable and configure Moltbot/Clawdbot memory  | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | search for persistent context. Use when       |                    |\\n|           |                                     | setting up memory, fixing \\\"goldfish brain,\\\"   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | or helping users configure memorySearch in    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | their config. Covers MEMORY.md, daily logs,   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | and vector search setup.                      |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? context-manager                  | Auto context management with seamless         | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | session switching. Monitors usage, triggers   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | at 85% threshold, automatically creates new   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | session with loaded memory. Zero user         |                    |\\n|           |                                     | intervention required. Trigger on \\\"context\\\",  |                    |\\n|           |                                     | \\\"memory\\\", \\\"session management\\\", \\\"context      |                    |\\n|           |                                     | limit\\\", \\\"memory transfer\\\".                    |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? multi-search-engine              | Multi search engine integration with 17       | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | engines (8 CN + 9 Global). Supports advanced  |                    |\\n|           |                                     | search operators, time filters, site search,  |                    |\\n|           |                                     | privacy engines, and WolframAlpha knowledge   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | queries. No API keys required.                |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? news-summary                     | This skill should be used when the user asks  | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | for news updates, daily briefings, or what's  |                    |\\n|           |                                     | happening in the world. Fetches news from     |                    |\\n|           |                                     | trusted international RSS feeds and can       |                    |\\n|           |                                     | create voice summaries.                       |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? Proactivity (Proactive Agent)    | Anticipates needs, keeps work moving, and     | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | improves through use so the agent gets more   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | proactive over time.                          |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? Self-Improving + Proactive Agent | Self-reflection + Self-criticism + Self-      | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | learning + Self-organizing memory. Agent      |                    |\\n|           |                                     | evaluates its own work, catches mistakes,     |                    |\\n|           |                                     | and improves permanently. Use when (1) a      |                    |\\n|           |                                     | command, tool, API, or operation fails; (2)   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | the user corrects you or rejects your work;   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | (3) you realize your knowledge is outdated    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | or incorrect; (4) you discover a better       |                    |\\n|           |                                     | approach; (5) the user explicitly installs    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | or references the skill for the current task. |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? skill-finder-cn                  | Skill ?????| Skill Finder. ???????????  | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | ClawHub Skills | Discover and install         |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ClawHub Skills.                               |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ???'???????????'?????????? |         |                    |\\n|           |                                     | Answers 'what skill can X', 'find a skill'.   |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ????????skill??ind skill?????skill.     |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? skill-vetter                     | Security-first skill vetting for AI agents.   | openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | Use before installing any skill from          |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ClawdHub, GitHub, or other sources. Checks    |                    |\\n|           |                                     | for red flags, permission scope, and          |                    |\\n|           |                                     | suspicious patterns.                          |                    |\\n| ??ready   | ?? tushare                          | tushare?????????????????????????????| openclaw-workspace |\\n|           |                                     | ??????????????????????????????????? |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ?????????????????????????????????? |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ???API?????????????????????????????|                    |\\n|           |                                     | ??????????????????????????????????? |                    |\\n|           |                                     | ???????                                     |                    |\\n+-----------+-------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------+--------------------+\\n\\nTip: use `npx clawhub` to search, install, and sync skills.\",\"_meta\":{\"runtime\":\"node\",\"runtimeVersion\":\"24.14.0\",\"hostname\":\"WIN-F6MBLNIG386\",\"name\":\"openclaw\",\"date\":\"2026-03-18T09:09:43.731Z\",\"logLevelId\":3,\"logLevelName\":\"INFO\",\"path\":{\"fullFilePath\":\"file:///C:/Users/Administrator/AppData/Roaming/npm/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944:46\",\"fileName\":\"subsyste